# Arabic RTL: Complete Right-to-Left Layout

## Rule

**When the app is in Arabic (RTL), the ENTIRE layout must follow RTL conventions:**

1. **Titles and headers** on the RIGHT side of cards, dialogs, sheets, panels, modals
2. **Icons** to the RIGHT of text (not left)
3. **Text alignment** to the right
4. **Navigation and tabs** flow right-to-left (first item on the right)
5. **Form labels** above their inputs, aligned right
6. **Date inputs** with calendar icon on the left, date text on the right

## Global CSS Rules (in `app/globals.css`)

The following rules are already implemented and MUST NOT be removed:

- `[dir="rtl"] { direction: rtl !important; text-align: right !important; }` — base RTL
- `[dir="rtl"] [data-slot="card-title"]` — card titles on right
- `[dir="rtl"] .flex.items-center:has(> svg)` — icon+text rows reverse to put icon on right
- `[dir="rtl"] .flex.items-center.gap-*` — all flex icon rows reverse
- `[dir="rtl"] [data-slot="tabs-trigger"]` — tab icons on right of labels

## When Adding New Components

1. **Any flex row with icon + text**: The global `:has(> svg)` rule handles this automatically
2. **New title components**: Add `data-slot="your-title"` and a rule in globals.css
3. **Headers with text-left or text-center**: Add `rtl:text-right` override
4. **Buttons with icons**: Icons will automatically appear on the right in RTL

## Scope

- **All pages**: Patient, professional, super-admin dashboards
- **All components**: Cards, dialogs, sheets, drawers, alerts, modals, tabs, navigation
- **All forms**: Labels, inputs, selects, date pickers
- **All platforms**: Desktop, tablet, mobile

## Logical Properties to Use

Always prefer logical properties that automatically adapt to RTL:

| LTR Property | Logical Property |
|--------------|------------------|
| `left-*` | `start-*` |
| `right-*` | `end-*` |
| `pl-*` | `ps-*` |
| `pr-*` | `pe-*` |
| `ml-*` | `ms-*` |
| `mr-*` | `me-*` |
| `border-l` | `border-s` |
| `border-r` | `border-e` |
| `inset-x-0 left-64` | `inset-y-0 start-0 end-0 md:start-64` |

## Do Not

- Add `text-left` without `rtl:text-right`
- Use physical properties (`left`, `right`, `ml-`, `mr-`, `pl-`, `pr-`) instead of logical (`start`, `end`, `ms-`, `me-`, `ps-`, `pe-`)
- Remove `!important` from globals.css RTL rules
- Override `flex-direction: row-reverse` in RTL contexts
- Use `justify-end` for RTL alignment (use `justify-start` — "start" is right in RTL)
- Use `fixed inset-0 left-64` — use `fixed inset-y-0 start-0 end-0 md:start-64` instead
